# WPF Validation Error Handling

- Do not use `MessageBox.Show` for form validation failures in procurement controls.
- Render validation feedback inline next to each offending field using dedicated error text elements (collapsed by default).
- Validate on submit with a control-level `Validate...` method and return early when invalid.
- Move keyboard focus to the first invalid field after submit to guide correction.
- On field `TextChanged`, hide the corresponding error when the value becomes valid.
- Keep this pattern aligned with `ProcurementResolve` and `ProcurementDispute`.
